---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "BC PNP Processing Times 2026: How Long Does It Take?";
const description =
    "Current BC PNP processing times for all streams. Learn how long provincial nomination, federal PR, and each stage takes in 2026, plus tips to avoid delays.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <article class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8">
            <!-- Header -->
            <header class="space-y-4 text-center">
                <div
                    class="inline-block bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mb-4"
                >
                    Updated January 2026
                </div>
                <h1
                    class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight"
                >
                    BC PNP <span class="text-green-600">Processing Times</span>
                </h1>
                <p
                    class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
                >
                    How long does it take to get nominated and become a
                    permanent resident? Here are the latest estimated processing
                    times for 2026.
                </p>
            </header>

            <!-- Timeline Overview -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 text-center">
                    Complete Timeline Overview
                </h3>
                <div
                    class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-2 sm:gap-4 text-sm"
                >
                    <div class="bg-slate-100 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">
                        <div class="font-bold text-slate-700">SIRS Pool</div>
                        <div class="text-slate-500">1-12 months</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-slate-300 hidden sm:block">â†’</div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-100 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">
                        <div class="font-bold text-blue-700">BC PNP</div>
                        <div class="text-blue-500">2-4 months</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-slate-300 hidden sm:block">â†’</div>
                    <div class="bg-green-100 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">
                        <div class="font-bold text-green-700">Federal PR</div>
                        <div class="text-green-500">5-18 months</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Main Content -->
            <div
                class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none bg-white p-8 sm:p-12 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm"
            >
                <h2>Stage 1: Time in SIRS Pool</h2>
                <p>
                    Before you get an invitation, you'll wait in the Skills
                    Immigration Registration System (SIRS). This time varies
                    greatly based on your score and the streams you qualify for.
                </p>

                <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto my-6">
                    <table class="min-w-full text-left text-sm">
                        <thead class="bg-gray-100 border-b border-gray-200">
                            <tr>
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900"
                                    >Your Score</th
                                >
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900"
                                    >Typical Wait Time</th
                                >
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900"
                                    >Notes</th
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
                            <tr class="bg-green-50">
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold">120+</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >1-4 weeks</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >Usually invited quickly</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold">100-119</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">1-3 months</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >Competitive range</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold">80-99</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">3-6 months</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >May need targeted draw</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold">Below 80</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600"
                                    >6-12+ months</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >Consider improving score</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-xl text-sm border border-blue-200 mb-8"
                >
                    <strong>ðŸ’¡ Priority Streams:</strong> If you qualify for BC PNP
                    Tech, Healthcare, or Childcare targeted draws, you may receive
                    invitations much faster regardless of score.
                </div>

                <h2>Stage 2: BC PNP Processing Times</h2>
                <p>
                    Once you receive an invitation and submit your complete
                    application, BC PNP begins processing. This is the time from
                    application submission to nomination decision.
                </p>

                <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto my-6">
                    <table class="min-w-full text-left text-sm">
                        <thead class="bg-gray-100 border-b border-gray-200">
                            <tr>
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900"
                                    >Stream</th
                                >
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900"
                                    >Processing Time</th
                                >
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900"
                                    >Notes</th
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium"
                                    >Skilled Worker</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >2-3 months</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >Standard processing</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium"
                                    >International Graduate</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >2-3 months</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >Standard processing</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-green-50">
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium"
                                    >BC PNP Tech</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >2-3 months</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >Often faster due to priority</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-green-50">
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium"
                                    >Health Authority</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >2-3 months</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >Priority processing</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium"
                                    >Entry Level & Semi-Skilled</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold"
                                    >3-4 months</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >More verification required</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium"
                                    >Entrepreneur Immigration</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold"
                                    >4-6 months</td
                                >
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500"
                                    >Business plan review</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-xl text-sm border border-slate-200 mb-8"
                >
                    <strong>Note:</strong> Processing time starts from when you submit
                    your <em>complete</em> application after receiving an invitationâ€”not
                    from when you register in SIRS.
                </div>

                <h2>Stage 3: Federal PR Processing</h2>
                <p>
                    After BC nominates you, you apply to the federal government
                    (IRCC) for permanent residence. This is often the longest
                    stage.
                </p>

                <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 not-prose my-6">
                    <div
                        class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-2xl"
                    >
                        <div
                            class="text-xs font-bold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2"
                        >
                            Express Entry BC
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-4xl font-black text-green-700 mb-2">
                            5-8 months
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-green-700 text-sm">
                            Online system. Much faster processing.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-green-700 mt-3 space-y-1">
                            <li>âœ“ +600 CRS points</li>
                            <li>âœ“ Guaranteed ITA</li>
                            <li>âœ“ Online application</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border border-slate-200 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                        <div
                            class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2"
                        >
                            Non-Express Entry
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-4xl font-black text-slate-700 mb-2">
                            11-18 months
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">
                            Paper-based/Portal. Slower processing.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-3 space-y-1">
                            <li>â€¢ Portal application</li>
                            <li>â€¢ Manual processing</li>
                            <li>â€¢ Longer wait times</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Total Timeline Examples</h2>

                <h3>Best Case Scenario (Express Entry BC + High Score)</h3>
                <div class="not-prose bg-green-50 p-5 rounded-xl mb-6">
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center text-sm">
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >SIRS: 2 weeks</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-green-600">+</span>
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >BC PNP: 2 months</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-green-600">+</span>
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >Federal EE: 5 months</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-green-600">=</span>
                        <span
                            class="bg-green-600 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded font-bold"
                            >~8 months total</span
                        >
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3>Typical Case Scenario (Skills Immigration)</h3>
                <div class="not-prose bg-blue-50 p-5 rounded-xl mb-6">
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center text-sm">
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >SIRS: 2 months</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-blue-600">+</span>
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >BC PNP: 3 months</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-blue-600">+</span>
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >Federal: 14 months</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-blue-600">=</span>
                        <span
                            class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded font-bold"
                            >~19 months total</span
                        >
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3>Challenging Case (ELSS + Low Score)</h3>
                <div class="not-prose bg-amber-50 p-5 rounded-xl mb-6">
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center text-sm">
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >SIRS: 6 months</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-amber-600">+</span>
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >BC PNP: 4 months</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-amber-600">+</span>
                        <span class="bg-white px-3 py-1 rounded"
                            >Federal: 16 months</span
                        >
                        <span class="text-amber-600">=</span>
                        <span
                            class="bg-amber-600 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded font-bold"
                            >~26 months total</span
                        >
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Factors That Cause Delays</h2>
                <p>Your application might move slower than average if:</p>

                <h3>BC PNP Stage Delays</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Incomplete Documents:</strong> Missing signatures,
                        blurry scans, or wrong forms
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Employer Verification Issues:</strong> BC PNP cannot
                        reach your employer to verify job offer
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Additional Document Requests:</strong> You take too
                        long to respond
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Complex Work History:</strong> Unusual business structures
                        or multiple employers
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>High Volume:</strong> Sudden spike in applications
                        after a large draw
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Federal Stage Delays</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Security Checks:</strong> Background screening taking
                        longer than usual
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Medical Issues:</strong> Additional medical exams
                        required
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Missing Police Certificates:</strong> Delays from
                        certain countries
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Name/DOB Errors:</strong> Inconsistencies between
                        documents
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Address Changes:</strong> Not updating your address
                        in the portal
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>How to Minimize Processing Time</h2>

                <h3>Before Applying</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Prepare documents early:</strong> Start gathering
                        employer documents when you register in SIRS
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Get fresh language test:</strong> Ensure results won't
                        expire during processing
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Obtain police certificates:</strong> Request from
                        all countries you lived in 6+ monthsâ€”some take months to arrive
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <h3>During BC PNP Processing</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Submit complete application:</strong> Don't leave
                        any field blank or document missing
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Inform your employer:</strong> Tell them BC PNP may
                        call to verifyâ€”they should respond quickly
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Check email daily:</strong> Respond to any requests
                        within 24 hours if possible
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Keep documents current:</strong> Update if passport/work
                        permit expires
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <h3>During Federal Processing</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Complete medical promptly:</strong> Book your panel
                        physician appointment immediately when requested
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Update personal info:</strong> Notify IRCC of any
                        address, job, or family changes
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Respond quickly:</strong> Any requests for additional
                        info should be addressed immediately
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Don't travel unnecessarily:</strong> Complex travel
                        history can trigger additional checks
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <div
                    class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-xl text-sm border border-green-200 mt-8"
                >
                    <strong>ðŸ’¡ Pro Tip:</strong> There's no paid "express processing"
                    option for BC PNP or federal PR. The only way to speed things
                    up is to qualify for Express Entry and submit perfect, complete
                    applications.
                </div>

                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

                <h3>Can I work while waiting for PR?</h3>
                <p>
                    Yes, if you have a valid work permit. After receiving your
                    BC PNP nomination, you can request a Work Permit Support
                    Letter to apply for a new work permit without an LMIA.
                </p>

                <h3>What if my work permit expires during processing?</h3>
                <p>
                    Apply for a new work permit before your current one expires.
                    Use the BC PNP nomination to support an LMIA-exempt work
                    permit application.
                </p>

                <h3>Can I check my application status?</h3>
                <p>
                    Yes. For BC PNP, log into your BC PNP Online account. For
                    federal PR, check your IRCC account or use the online status
                    tracker.
                </p>

                <h3>What happens if processing takes longer than expected?</h3>
                <p>
                    Some delays are normal. If your application significantly
                    exceeds stated processing times, you can submit a web form
                    inquiry to BC PNP or IRCC.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- CTA -->
            <div
                class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-600 to-green-700 p-8 rounded-2xl text-center text-white"
            >
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Calculate Your Score</h2>
                <p class="text-green-100 mb-6">
                    Higher scores mean faster invitations. See where you stand.
                </p>
                <a
                    href="/bc-pnp-calculator"
                    class="inline-block bg-white text-green-700 font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-green-50 transition-colors"
                >
                    Use the Calculator â†’
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>
